{"key":"processedPost-6899148","value":{"id":6899148,"first":6897688,"last":6936482,"when":1178849021,"utime":"05/11/07 05:03 AM","content":"Casing layer sterility has nothing to do with trichoderma.  You're supposed to pasteurize casing material.  If you sterilize it, you raise the risk factor for trich by a factor of at least ten.  Air exchange and proper pasteurization is the key to avoiding trichoderma, not sterility.<br />In addition, if the outbreak occured before first flush, the trich was in your spawn or bulk substrate and simply sporulated in the casing layer.<br />RR","title":"Re: De-casing a tray to escape a trich attack"}}